      <hedline>
        <hl1>Balancing the Pay Scale</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Olivier de Messieres letter on June 10 Economic View column on income inequality; says growing income gap is national threat; adds reducing it should be national priority (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Income Inequality, Writ Larger'' (Economic View, June 10), which reported a study's finding that the top 1 percent of American earners reaped more than 17 percent of gross personal income:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Income Inequality, Writ Larger'' (Economic View, June 10), which reported a study's finding that the top 1 percent of American earners reaped more than 17 percent of gross personal income:</p>
        <p>The fact that annual salary of a high school teacher can be far less than the weekly pay of a big-league baseball pitcher is very relevant to the performance of our education system, and therefore to our nation's competitiveness and security. Income inequality shrinks the pool of qualified teachers.</p>
        <p>The growing income gap is a national threat. Reducing it should be the national priority.</p>
        <p>OLIVIER DE MESSIÃˆRES  Boyds, Md., June 11</p>
      </block>
